Why the BT Investment Management Share Price Blasted Off on Friday Money Morning 10/04/2015What Happened to BT Investment Management Ltd’s Share Price?
Shares in global fund manager BT Investment Management Ltd [ASX:BTT] soared by a massive 7% on Friday, strongly outpacing a resilient Aussie stock market. Today’s price action caps a sensational 12 months for BT, which has seen its share price rise by 50% over the past year.
Why Did This Happen to BTT Shares?
This morning BT revealed that its funds under management (FUM) grew solidly in the three months to March. At the end of 2014, BT’s FUM sat at $70 billion. FUM has now grown beyond $77 billion. BT said the quarter’s inflows will boost fee income by $11.5m this year.
This shows us the business is performing well and raises the scope for a stronger dividend payment. That’s why investors were happy to bid the stock up well in Friday’s trading.
What Now for BT Investment Management Ltd?
BT remains in a strong position to continue growing its business. Its investment in global distribution and product development should support profit and share price growth.
But you can’t expect BT’s share price to keep growing at the remarkable rate of the past 12 months. Things could get tougher for BT investors into the back half of 2015.
If you’ve got the right tolerance for risk, you can find even attractive businesses in the small-cap end of the Aussie stock market. If you’re seeking big potential rewards from exciting stocks that trade now for mere cents, go here to find out more.
Cheers, Tim Dohrmann
Small-Cap Analyst, Australian Small-Cap Investigator
Join Money Morning on Google+ 
   



