Introduction 


 This content is largely derived from Company
sources (e.g. the Company's annual report,
website etc.). Its publication has not been authorised by the Company. Links to the
sources of all content have been provided. All information presented here is publicly
available information.




1. About 
BT Investment Management Limited is one of the largest ASX-listed pure investment managers with a market capitalisation of around $2.73 billion and funds under management of $84.0 billion as at 30 September 2016. Investing is the Company’s only business and it operates a multi-boutique structure that provides for a full investment autonomy. BT Investment does not subscribe to a ‘house view’ and allows the freedom for each boutique to apply discretion in determining its investment process and philosophy and hence there is no influence from management on any investment decision.[1]




2. Business model 
The company operates in the following divisions:[2]
 




