Online and brokers channel


Cash NPAT was $156.0M, an increase of 18% compared to the prior period while statutory NPAT increased 12% to $142.0M. The result has been achieved due to higher average FUM driven by strong inflows, together with increased fee margins and higher performance fees.  Cash EPS increased 15% to 50.8 cents.
The increase in total revenue was driven by

higher revenue margins
strong support from institutional clients in the form of inflows
continued flows into US pooled vehicles
strong flows into its fixed income strategies





