6. History 
1969[7]
The Company was originally established as Ord-BT Ltd.
 
1978  
Became fully owned by Bankers Trust Company (New York), when it changed its name to BT Australia Ltd.
 
1990   
The Bankers Trust Corporation, BT Australia went through ownership change to Deutsche Bank.
 
1999   
The Bankers Trust Corporation, BT Australia went through ownership change to Principal Financial Group.
 
2002   
Westpac acquired BT Financial Group (BTFG) from Principal including the funds management  division. Also folded into the BT funds management business at the time was the Rothschild Asset Management and Westpac Investment Management business.
 
2007  
The investment management arm of the broader BT Financial Group listed as a separate investment management business as BT Investment Management (BTIM) with Westpac retaining majority ownership.
 
2011   
BTIM expanded offshore by acquiring J O Hambro Capital Management (JOHCM) a London based boutique active equity manager.
 
2012   
Amended Dividend Reinvestment Plan Rules, Amended Constitution.
On-market purchase program for Employee Equity Plans
 
2015  
Westpac reduced its holding to approximately 31%, providing increased size and diversity of BTIM’s shareholder base, an increased free float resulting in greater liquidity of BTIM shares and eligibility for consideration in key market indices. Westpac’s and BTIM’s relationship remains strong and mutually beneficial
 
2016   
BTIM established Australian-based Global Equities boutique




